<subSubSection id="C35436B80B1EFFD3FF2DB9E596F5A94E" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF165330B1EFFD3FF2DB9E595B3A931" blockId="15.[136,1452,1266,1654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FF2DB9E59720AA34" bold="true" box="[189,353,1266,1292]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">Discussion:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF18C20B1EFFD3FEF1B9E4944FAA36" author="Howard, R. A." box="[353,526,1267,1294]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref17096" refString="Howard, R. A. (1952) The vegetation of the Grenadines, Windward Islands, British West Indies. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 174: 1 - 129." type="journal article" year="1952">Howard (1952)</bibRefCitation>
failed to mention that this species is present on 
<collectingCountry id="F35925A30B1EFFD3FBA2B9E492A4AA35" box="[1074,1253,1267,1293]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">The Grenadines</collectingCountry>
and he later only reports 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E1EB00B1EFFD3FF71B800944EAA09" authorityName="Karsten" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[225,527,1303,1329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Mammillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mammillaris">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FF71B800944EAA09" box="[225,527,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">Mammillaria mammillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the island of Canouan (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF18C20B1EFFD3FCE2B8009215AA0A" author="Howard, R. A." box="[882,1108,1303,1330]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" refId="ref17132" refString="Howard, R. A. (1989) Flora of the Lesser Antilles, Vol. 5. President and Fellows of Harvard College, Jamaica Plain, Massachusetts, 604 pp." type="book" year="1989">Howard 1989: 406</bibRefCitation>
). Plumier, in his unpublished manuscript, reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E1EB00B1EFFD3FEEBB82B9470AA6D" authorityName="Karsten" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[379,561,1339,1365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Mammillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mammillaris">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FEEBB82B9470AA6D" box="[379,561,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">M. mammillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the islands of Canouan and Carriacou. We confirmed the occurrence of this species only in Canouan. We also discovered 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E1EB00B1EFFD3FD22B8779524AA41" authorityName="Karsten" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[690,869,1375,1401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Mammillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mammillaris">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FD22B8779524AA41" box="[690,869,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">M. mammillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on further islands of 
<collectingCountry id="F35925A30B1EFFD3FBC2B8489347AA41" box="[1106,1286,1375,1401]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">The Grenadines</collectingCountry>
, although with fragmented distribution. The species is locally common, but populations are small (usually less than 50 individuals). It favours inaccessible coastal cliffs or steep rocky areas close to the sea. Just once, on Ronde island, did we find it growing in grasses on a ridge with underlying rocky soils (
<figureCitation id="137579B60B1EFFD3FCA5B8DC95C8AADD" box="[821,905,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[136,229,2002,2024]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1120,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-37@14.[151,1436,1120,1978]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11 Mammillaria mammillaris (Hoxey 1704.04) growing in grasses, Ronde Island." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5420324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5420324/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). The plants we encountered had an occasional flower or red fruit, neither of which protrude beyond the spines (
<figureCitation id="137579B60B1EFFD3FCCCB8F895A4A931" box="[860,997,1519,1545]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 12" captionStart-1="FIGURE 13" captionStartId-0="15.[136,229,1198,1220]" captionStartId-1="16.[136,229,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,190,1174]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,245,1334]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@15.[151,1436,190,1174]" captionTargetId-1="figure-39@16.[151,1436,245,1334]" captionTargetPageId-0="15" captionTargetPageId-1="16" captionText-0="FIGURE 12. Flowering Mammillaria mammillaris (Hoxey 1681.03) on Canouan." captionText-1="FIGURE 13. Mammillaria mammillaris (Hoxey 1704.04) with fruit on Ronde Island." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5420326" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5420329" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5420326/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5420329/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF165330B1EFFD3FF2DBB0496F5A94E" blockId="15.[136,1452,1266,1654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FF2DBB04951AA915" bold="true" box="[189,859,1554,1581]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">
Note of the typification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E1EB00B1EFFD3FD92BB059574A915" authorityName="Karsten" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[514,821,1554,1581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Mammillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mammillaris">
<emphasis id="B93AB9210B1EFFD3FD92BB059574A915" bold="true" box="[514,821,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="40">Mammillaria mammillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
:—
</emphasis>
The lectotypification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF18C20B1EFFD3FB76BB0493E7A915" author="Wijnands, D. O." box="[1254,1446,1555,1581]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" refId="ref18445" refString="Wijnands, D. O. (1983) The botany of the Commelins. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, 232 pp." type="book" year="1983">Wijnands (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, who used the illustration by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF18C20B1EFFD3FE57BB209489A96A" author="Commelijn, J." box="[455,712,1591,1618]" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" refId="ref16563" refString="Commelijn, J. (1697) Horti medici amstelodamensis rariorum tam orientalis, Pars Prima. P. &amp; J. Blaeu, Amsterdam, 220 pp." type="book" year="1697">Commelijn (1697: 105</bibRefCitation>
, t.55) is superseded by the previous one given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF18C20B1EFFD3FB69BB2096F1A94E" author="Mottram, R." pageId="15" pageNumber="40" refId="ref17790" refString="Mottram, R. (1980) The Mammillaria index. Whitestone Gardens Ltd., Sutton-under-Whitestone-cliffe, Thirsk, 103 pp." type="book" year="1980">Mottram (1980: 51)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
